==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trilobite
<hw>Tri"lo*bite</hw> <pr>(tr⟦imac⟧"l⟦osl⟧*b⟦imac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. F. <ets>trilobite</ets>. See <er>Trilobate</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>Any one of numerous species of extinct
arthropods belonging to the order Trilobita. Trilobites were very common
in the Silurian and Devonian periods, but became extinct at the close of
the Paleozoic. So named from the three lobes usually seen on each
segment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trilobitic</ent>⟦br⟧
